      • setEnabled

        public void setEnabled(boolean v)
        Description copied from interface: Trace
        Enables or disables this trace.

        If the trace is enabled then it will keep track of value changes on the parent probe. These values are then accessible via Trace.getValues().

        If the trace is disabled then value changes on the parent probe are ignored and are not included in the list returned by Trace.getValues().

        Specified by:
        setEnabled in interface Trace<T>

      • getDelay

        public long getDelay()
        Description copied from interface: Trace
        Returns the minimum time delay before a probe value change is taken into account. In other words, the minumum time delay before a probe value change is included in the list returned by by Trace.getValues().

        Default is Trace.DEFAULT_DELAY if not specified otherwise.

        Specified by:
        getDelay in interface Trace<T>
        Returns:
        the minimum time delay before a probe value change is taken into account

      • setDelay

        public void setDelay(long delay)
        Description copied from interface: Trace
        Updates the minimum time delay before a probe value change is taken into account.

        If the delay is increased, then some trace values may be removed.

        Specified by:
        setDelay in interface Trace<T>

      • getValues

        public List<TraceItem<T>> getValues()
        Description copied from interface: Trace
        Returns an unmodifiable list containing TraceItems ordered chronologically.

        The returned list will not necessarily contain an item for every possible time, but instead it will contain a new item each time the value of this trace changes.
        Additionally, the minimum time difference between two items in the list is Trace.getDelay().

        Specified by:
        getValues in interface Trace<T>
        Returns:
        an unmodifiable list containing TraceItems ordered chronologically
